53.0	Chickenpox	Chickenpox	Chickenpox (or chicken pox) is a highly contagious illness caused by primary infection with varicella zoster virus (VZV). It usually starts with vesicular skin rash mainly on the body and head rather than at the periphery and becomes itchy, raw pockmarks, which mostly heal without scarring. On examination, the observer typically finds lesions at various stages of healing.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Varicela_Aranzales.jpg/230px-Varicela_Aranzales.jpg
